
[1]commiserate

   COMMISERATE, v.t.

   1. To pity; to compassionate; to feel sorrow, pain or regret for
   another in distress; applied to persons.

   We should commiserate those who groan beneath the weight of age,
   disease or want.

   2. To regret; to pity; to be sorry for; as, to commiserate our mutual
   ignorance.
